# Secrets Configuration
# =====================
# Copy this file to .secrets and fill in your values
# The .secrets file is gitignored and will not be committed
#
# Usage: cp .secrets.example .secrets

# =============================================================================
# TESSIE API (Required for Fleet API features)
# =============================================================================
# Generate your access token at: https://dash.tessie.com/settings/api
#
# Your Tessie Pro Lifetime account provides:
# - Unlimited API polling at no cost
# - Access to Tesla Fleet API, Fleet Telemetry, and Tessie APIs
# - Automatic vehicle wake-up and error handling
#
TESSIE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_tessie_token_here

# =============================================================================
# COMED OPOWER API (Optional - for actual meter data)
# =============================================================================
# Provides actual electricity usage and costs from your ComEd smart meter.
# This is the same data that appears on your monthly bill.
#
# See docs/COMED_OPOWER_SETUP.md for detailed setup instructions.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RECOMMENDED: Interactive Setup (no secrets needed here)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Run the setup script locally - it will prompt for credentials:
#   1. Set OPOWER_ENABLED=true in .env
#   2. Install locally: pip install httpx python-dotenv
#   3. Run locally: python scripts/comed_opower_setup.py
#   4. Enter credentials and MFA code when prompted
#   5. Collector auto-detects cache file within 30 seconds
#
# The script creates .comed_opower_cache.json with your session.
# No credentials need to be stored in this file!
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ALTERNATIVE: Bearer Token (Manual extraction, expires in ~20 min)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# To get the token:
#   1. Log into secure.comed.com in your browser
#   2. Navigate to "View My Usage"
#   3. Open DevTools (F12) â†’ Network tab
#   4. Find any request to cec.opower.com
#   5. Copy the Authorization header value
#
# COMED_BEARER_TOKEN=Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6...

